The moderates within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, joined by the agrarian wing, are unable to defeat Hugenberg in a vote. This is in part due to Hugenberg's efforts of consolidating power within the party organizations. The agrarian representatives in the party finally had enough with Hugenberg's "all or nothing" strategy, especially after he collapsed the right-wing coalition exactly a year ago. 

The anti-Hugenberg forces within the party have all left to form a new <i>Konservative Volkspartei</i> (Conservative People's Party). It is a question of how long this party would last, with some members rather wanting to affiliate with the special interest parties.